                Upon joining Precise Systems, you will be eligible for all employee benefits afforded by our personnel policy.  The key features of our benefits program specifically tailored for you are:
            </p>
            <ul class="mb-10 bullet-list">
                <li>
                    <span id="accrual-rate">
                        Employee Managed Leave accrued at the rate of <$client.tForWhomUserInfo.Accrual_Rate> hours per pay period. 
                    </span><sup style="font-size:100%">1</sup>
                </li>
                <li>
                    Holidays and Sick Leave per policy.
                </li>
                <li>
                    401(k) retirement plan with company contributions.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Medical, dental and vision insurance coverage.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Training/education benefit.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Group life insurance coverage. 
                </li>
                <li>
                    Accidental death and dismemberment insurance coverage.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Short-term disability insurance coverage.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Long-term disability insurance coverage.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Upon your request, the provisions and eligibility requirements for each of our employee benefits (including our 401(k) retirement plan) will be explained to you in detail.  Your employment is contingent upon government funding, your ability to qualify to work on our customers’ contracts, your obtaining and maintaining the requisite DoD security clearances (within a reasonable time period), which will allow you to perform the duties for which you are being hired, and successfully passing all of Precise Systems’ pre-employment screening.  Additionally, your employment is contingent upon completing the I-9 Form (Employment Eligibility Verification) establishing your identity and legal right to work in the United States by your third day of employment.
            </p>
            <p id="expiration-date-content">
                You will be an "at will" employee, which means that either you or Precise Systems is free to terminate your employment at any time, with or without cause and with or without notice.  If we do not receive your signed acceptance by <span class="long-date"><$client.tForWhomUserInfo.Offer_Expiration_Date></span>, we will consider you to have declined and this offer will be rescinded.
            </p>
            <p>
                We look forward to having you as a member of the Precise Systems team.  We are certain that you will enjoy a very long and successful career with Precise Systems, and that we will benefit immensely from your service.
            </p>
            <p>
                Sincerely,
            </p>
